  • Justin C. Frye was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

State of Wisconsin vs. Justin Frye					Hon. Eugene Harrington
15 CF 77								Laurel Dean, Court Reporter

Bruce P. Anderson

On record at 08:17am, court calls case and appearances. Thomas H. Frost appears for the State of Wisconsin. Justin Frye appears in person with Bruce Anderson.  Court speaks to the parties re: prior convictions. Court finds the def. freely and knowingly waives his right to have the jury decide prior convictions of both counts.  State speaks to the court re: witnesses.  Off record. Back on the record at 08:23am. Court speaks re: witnesses and Mr. Frost previously representing Mr. Frye. Atty Anderson speaks to the court.   Court speaks to the parties. State makes statement.  Court speaks to Mr. Frye. Mr. Frye stipulates to prior convictions being found by the court.  Court speaks re: jury instructions.  Off record. 
On record at 08:57am. Bailiff seats jurors.  Court calls case and appearances.  Clerk swears in jurors.  Court speaks to the jury.  Court begins questioning.   Court questions Juror Paske. Jurors that have served on a previous jury raise hands. Court begins questioning.  Juror Jacobs raises hand. Court questions.  Juror Haseleu raises hand, court questions.  Jurors Feiertag and Beach raises hand, court questions. Jurors raise hands re: OWI questioning from the court. Mr. Zach raises hand. Court speaks to Mr. Zach. Juror Beach raises hand, court questions.  Jurors raise hands re: consuming alcohol. Court questions. Mr. Zach is excused. Juror Dullinger is called and seated.  No further questions from the court. State questions jurors.  Atty Anderson questions the jurors.   Attorneys exercise their strikes.  Court calls jurors selected.  Clerk swears in Jurors. Off record.
Back on record at 9:55am. Court speaks to Jurors.  State begins with opening statement. Atty Anderson give opening statement.  State calls Officer Tia Hartl to the stand. Clerk swears in Officer Hartl.  State begins questioning.  Objection from Atty Anderson, over ruled.  State continues questioning.  Objection from Atty Anderson. Sustained. State continues questioning.   Jury stands down.  Atty Anderson speaks to the court.    Atty Anderson asks for a mistrial.  State makes statement.  Rebuttal from Atty Anderson.  Motion for mistrial is denied.  Court speaks to the parties.  Jury returns. Court speaks to the jury.  State continues questioning.  No further questions from the state. Cross from Atty Anderson.  Nothing further from Atty Anderson. Re-direct from the State. Re-cross from Atty Anderson.  Nothing further. Witness is excused.  State rests.  Jury stands down.  Outside the presence of the jury. Atty Anderson speaks to the court.  Atty Anderson makes a motion to dismiss both counts.  Court speaks to the parties.  State speaks to the court. Court denies motions. Court speaks his findings.  Atty Anderson makes a motion to dismiss. State speaks to the court.  Atty Anderson speaks to the court.  Court finds that the parties did not comply with the scheduling order. Court speaks to the def. re: waiving his rights to testify.  The court finds the def. freely and knowingly waives his rights.  Off record.  Back on record at 11:18. Atty Anderson calls defendant Justin Frye to the stand. Atty Anderson begins questioning. Nothing further from Atty Anderson. Cross from the state.  No further questions. Re-direct. Nothing further. Witness is excused.  Atty Anderson calls Officer Tia Hartl. Nothing further. Cross from the State. Nothing further. Witness is excused. Defense rests.  Evidence is closed.  State speaks to the court. State moves to reopen the evidence and allow the state to play the DVD.  Atty Anderson argues.  Court grants the motion to reopen the evidence.   Off record to go over jury instructions.  Back on record to go over jury instructions.  Back on record at 12:45. Court speaks to the parties. 
Jury returns at 12:50. Court speaks to Jury and calls case. Clerk begins video. Video is complete. State asks that the video be put into the court file.  Atty Anderson calls Officer Hartl.  Nothing further. State questions Officer Hartl.  Witness is excused. Jury is excused.   State & Atty Anderson speak re: driving while revoked in parking lot. Court speaks ruling.  Jury instruction will not be changed.  Off record at 1:23pm. Back on record at 1:28pm.  Court speaks to parties re: jury instructions.  
Jury returns. Court begins jury instructions.  State gives closing argument. Atty Anderson gives closing argument. Rebuttal from the State. Court gives final instructions.   Clerk swears in bailiff. Jury is given the case at 2:18pm.  Off record discussions on a question from the jury.  Back on record at 3:11-question from Jury re: revocation charge.  Jury returns-court answers question.  
Verdict:
Count 1-guilty.	
Count 2-Not guilty. 
Court accepts verdict.  
Court address count 2, Motion to change verdict as to count 1 by Atty Anderson.  Argument by State. Court finds that there is evidence for count 1.  Motion is denied.  Court finds there have been 3 previous convictions. 
Court orders a PSI as to count 1. Agent need not appear.
